<span id="freeTextContainer3963799116928891566">This 2 book story is my favorite fantasy novel of all time. I reread it every couple of years. While it&apos;s obviously well written, because Donaldson never puts out a book that isn&apos;t, I think it&apos;s the core of each character that moves me the most. Each recognizes their imperfections, doubts their strength, but just keeps moving forward and accomplishing more than they thought possible. And while recognizing their own weaknesses, they also recognize the strengths in each other and band together to </span>
  <span id="freeText3963799116928891566" style="display:none">This 2 book story is my favorite fantasy novel of all time. I reread it every couple of years. While it's obviously well written, because Donaldson never puts out a book that isn't, I think it's the core of each character that moves me the most. Each recognizes their imperfections, doubts their strength, but just keeps moving forward and accomplishing more than they thought possible. And while recognizing their own weaknesses, they also recognize the strengths in each other and band together to build an "us" that is far greater than the sum of each "me."</span>
