<div id="review_3215042695" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3215042695" />
    <a title="Jen526" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2230469-jen526"><img alt="Jen526" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3215042695?book_show_action=true">May 24, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jen526" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jen526" href="/user/show/2230469-jen526">Jen526</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2230469-jen526?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer3215042695&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3215042695" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17183565786508358193">Definitely not a book for those who lean toward faster pacing or action. This book is almost entirely palace intrigue, with the characters mostly just having lots of questions, with most true answers put off until the next volume. I enjoyed it a lot as a bit of a different sort of take on both a portal fantasy and a coming of age story. Our heroine is someone who is pulled into another world to be a &quot;savior&quot;, but has no real skills to bring to the table and has to immediately contend with multip</span>
  <span id="freeText17183565786508358193" style="display:none">Definitely not a book for those who lean toward faster pacing or action. This book is almost entirely palace intrigue, with the characters mostly just having lots of questions, with most true answers put off until the next volume. I enjoyed it a lot as a bit of a different sort of take on both a portal fantasy and a coming of age story. Our heroine is someone who is pulled into another world to be a "savior", but has no real skills to bring to the table and has to immediately contend with multiple factions wanting to use her for their own aims - some of whom believe she's the savior, some who think she's an enemy, and others who dismiss her as a mistake and waste of time. Add to this that she, herself, is emotionally damaged without an ounce of personal self-esteem, and the story mostly becomes about Teresa moving from a passive non-entity going down a path of least resistance to someone who pushes past her perceptions of her own limitations and tries to pursue what she thinks is the right course of action as much as she can. I tend to be a fan of books where the story is as much about the characters working through their own inner demons as it is about the external save-the-world plot, and this book is a fairly textbook example of that sort of approach.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17183565786508358193" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

